    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-09-13T04:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-09-13T04:30:00-05:00" n="359"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d359">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1115/767: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Commander in Chief of the United States Asiatic Fleet</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Yarnell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Chief of Naval Operations</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Leahy</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="26" xml:id="d359fn26">Copy transmitted to the Department by
                        the Navy Department.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-09-13T17:30:00+08:00"
                            >September 13, 1937—5:30 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 13—1:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>0013. To enable largest possible number nationals to evacuate China ports via <hi
                        rend="italic">Canopus, Chaumont</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Gold Star</hi>
                    all officers’ dependents proceeding United States will be left in northern
                    ports, <hi rend="italic">Canopus</hi> will return to northern ports via Hong
                    Kong and Woosung, then proceed Kobe with these dependents proceeding United
                    States commercially. <hi rend="italic">Canopus</hi> will then return Manila via
                    China ports evacuating nationals as necessary.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
